    "description": {
        "en-US": "This add-on is an ugly attempt at fixing <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/image-zoom/\">Image Zoom</a> version 0.6.3.1-signed.1-signed.\n\n<strong>Version 0.1.1 should fix the everything-is-not-working-anymore issue</strong>\n\n--\n\n<strong>The fixing addresses two issues:</strong>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/46d4ecb3ac6e5426e172cb78a5a8067128567b37bc2bceeb43463b63cd637ed7/https%3A//github.com/jasadams/imagezoom/issues/33\">#33</a> / <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/6b4e1b9edc5c46a303347ae8404e09cb7a3026cdc50a188715e44f7f19533909/https%3A//github.com/jasadams/imagezoom/issues/34\">#34</a> (images being cropped on top when zoomed)</li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/92403f4924db1d31dcffa4386a000c29ce9adbec2a19955aadaa156dd351a276/https%3A//github.com/jasadams/imagezoom/issues/23\">#23</a> (right clicking sets width and height styles)</li></ul>\n<strong>Two questions you might ask:</strong>\n<ul><li><i>It seems ugly, should I even try to use this add-on?</i></li></ul>Yup, most definitely. If one of those issues is blocking you, this add-on will provide you a work-ish version where the original add-on just doesn't work anymore, without changing anything else.\n<ul><li><i>Why so ugly tho?</i></li></ul>Because the original add-on is old and need to be fully rewritten to fit with the current Firefox UI and current add-on API. Those fixes don't even try to improve that situation, they just provide a most lazy way to make the original add-on survive a bit longer. Also those fixes will only work on the typical basic cases. As soon as it get complicated they won't do any much more than the original add-on. And finally, yeah...  the code is just ugly, let's be honest here.\n\n--\n\nAs soon as somebody decides to take over the original add-on and do a better job at fixing it or rewriting it, this add-on will disappear.\n\nMeanwhile you can still submit issues or questions to the github repo <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/6123281751b4daae8fcb124d3afcc2cd5caae5a52291b3304174263e673d33c7/https%3A//github.com/roger21/imagezoomuglyfixes\">https://github.com/roger21/imagezoomuglyfixes</a>"
    },
